				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hello Mages!
<br />
    I come from another realm, but while looking through the new cookie cutter spells of all classes I sorta though about an idea that would be neat for mages! Not sure this would belong here or really in the spell department since it seems to blend with both so feel free to move it. Anyhow the to the idea...
<br />

<br />
Okay first the though sorta stemmed from the idea of a short duration pet like Dyzil's Deafening Decoy and some AA I recalled that somewhat uberfied a pet. Anyhow the thought was to give mages a new spell series (one for each of the types of elements) that would sacrafice their current pet (would require an active pet of the specific element) and as well as a large amount of mana and call forth a *extremely* powerful elemental pet. The pet itself would do much more damage. (I'm not really gonna put numbers into this, but something that would perhaps be on par or close to a the equivalent of a player off the class the pet is.) But on the downside the pet would not be quiet as stable, and consequently have a short duration. (Again don't want to put numbers into this, but the though is of something that will last a somewhere in the neighborhood of 1-3 minutes, long enough for a short fight.) The downside to the pet is that the cost of the mana increase for power woudl be fairly significant. Somewhere in the range of possibly half a mana pool, but not so much that the magician wouldn't be unable to do a continue blasting for the duration if coming from full mana. The concept would primarly be for boss encounters, and for fun. Also the pet *must* be gigantic whlie in this mode! <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" /> Anyhow just a idea I wish to share that might add some fun.
<br />

<br />
Fantazia Er`Hed of The Nameless 
<br />
(Formely Discordant Screams of Mithaniel Marr)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
